State troopers are investigating the discovery of a body in a dirt median on the side of northbound Interstate 17 near Thunderbird Road in Phoenix on April 17, 2020, according to the Arizona Department of Public Safety. (Photo: Arizona Department of Transportation)

State troopers are investigating the discovery of a body on Friday morning on the side of Interstate 17 in north Phoenix, according to Bart Graves, a spokesman for Arizona Department of Public Safety.

The body was found off the right shoulder of I-17, in a dirt median near Thunderbird Road, according to Graves.

Further details were not immediately available.

All lanes, except for the HOV lane and the far left lane, have been closed for investigation.

